## Context

- Forty-third run — Covered 5 projects with 6 new journal entries and 4 new tasks.
- Journal #1088 (rb1-loss-pancancer-dependency-atlas):
  - **RB1-loss SL initial literature review:** CDK2 inhibition retains activity in RB1-loss models (NatComm 2025). Aurora A/B kinase SL validated (Cancer Discovery 2019). CHK1+WEE1 combo effective in NEPC (Oncogene 2024). INX-315 Phase 1/2 in CCNE1-amp tumors, FDA FTD for ovarian. No trial explicitly selects for RB1-loss.
- Journal #1089 (rb1-loss-pancancer-dependency-atlas):
  - **CDK2 clinical landscape for RB1:** eLife 2025 models CDK2i beyond CDK4/6i progression. Cell Reports 2025 review. INX-315 ASCO 2026 data expected (study completion Jun 2026).
- Journal #1090 (wrn-msi-pancancer-atlas):
  - **VVD-214/RO7589831 JMC publication (2025):** Full med chem paper. Covalent C727 engagement. Phase 1: 4 PRs in 32 evaluable MSI pts (DCR 68.8%). Three-drug WRN race continues.
- Journal #1091 (crc-kras-dependencies):
  - **Erasca pipeline updates:** ERAS-0015 confirmed/unconfirmed PRs at 8mg QD. H1 2026 update imminent. Erasca teased 2026 catalysts (Mar 1 conference). ERAS-4001 US Patent 12,552,813 (Feb 24, 2026). VS-7375 AACR 2026 preclinical poster PR007.
- Journal #1092 (pancancer-ferroptosis-atlas):
  - **FSP1+HDAC persister ferroptosis (Science Advances 2025):** Cancer persisters upregulate FSP1. HDAC+FSP1/GPX4 inhibitor combos may eliminate drug-resistant persisters. Nature Genetics 2025 ferroptosis perspective. icFSP1 still preclinical.
- Journal #1093 (tp53-hotspot-allele-dependencies):
  - **Rezatapopt NEJM full publication (Feb 26, 2026, PMID 41740031):** Phase 1 data. Responses in 8 tumor types (Y220C-mutant, KRAS-WT). Phase 2 enrollment completing Q1 2026. NDA Q1 2027.
